<br>
Necro, Someone to lead Necro Group and someone to res on island 8.  3 Alts - Out of way until you close bridge.<br>
<br>
With 2 people you need Necro with res crystal and someone to jump.<br>
<br>
Done it both ways and your right, its much better to have the alts parked up there, however, if your guild doesnt have 3 alts to burn.  The necro run strategy requires no alts (1 Res type alt on Drake island if you dont want to burn the crystal).  However, as you say it does require a necro main that doesnt screw up and forget to go up and refresh his corpse. <p>Cereberial Cortex<BR>Illusionist<BR>Desperate Measures<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwoonx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#333333>(7/18/02 7:58:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Restarting a 7th isle Plane of Sky raid at any time</span><hr size=1> Simpler way i see it once you can get let's say a necro and cleric twinks up there. Both log on, necro suicide (real xp death), pops in bazaar, get invited by someone who's gonna port up with a wizzy in group. cleric res necro, boom, you're rdy. Not like I plan on ever going to sky ever ever ever again, but could help others ;P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uizarek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izarek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#333333>(7/18/02 9:29:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Restarting a 7th isle Plane of Sky raid at any time</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Actually a &quot;normal&quot; bridge you need three characters.<br>
<br>
Necro, Someone to lead Necro Group and someone to res on island 8. 3 Alts - Out of way until you close bridge.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's not true.  You only need two, and no jumping required:<br>
<br>
Necro and rezer duel, necro loses, goes to bind point where a wizard (or actually any character who is going to be the leader of the group, wizard is logical choice) is waiting to invite you and give you the one coffin you need to invite the raid necro.  The wizard is the third character to lead, but doesn't need to be in sky.<br>
<br>
The necro gets rezzed (since it was a duel, revive will suffice so a 46 cleric or pally is enough) and is back up in Drake island.  The wizard is the leader of the group and can port people up to the 1st island.  Cleric goes with him as part of the first group so they can revive dueled bodies on 1st island to be summoned.  2 people only.  No extra ingredients other than what the raid porting up needs.<br>
<br>
Having someone jump off has drawbacks:<br>
- Requires 2 people with essence emerald, or 3 people without everytime a raid is restarted, plus 1 more coffin than the rest of the raid needs to get the jumper back to drake island.  Mine uses exactly as many coffins as there are people coming to the raid, not including the 2 alts.  Both scenarios burn a port up slot (1/6th of a sky stone as it were) on the initial port up.<br>
- For the 2 person jumper strategy you require a 53 necro.  Mine only takes a 46 necro or 51 SK and a 46 cleric or paladin.<br>
- A much higher risk of screwing up the setup.  When jumping off all it takes is the jumper or the necro going LD to screw the whole thing.  Since the jumper zones twice that could easily happen.  My strategy can only get screwed up if the necro or rezzer go LD for several minutes after the first duel and the corpse timer of the necro expires.  If anyone goes LD during the bridge, you just repeat the process.<br>
<br>
There are a few ways to handle getting your sky crown for your epic.  My strategy fits my needs because:<br>
- I don't have to do a sky raid myself, just piggyback onto an existing one before it breaks up.<br>
- I can get my mage crown by hunting for it without putting any friends or guildies (or myself) through any pain or suffering.  By burning two alts (which true can be significant) I can turn a mages biggest nightmare (right Nahualli? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) into a quickie 2 - 3 hour raid whenever I can get people willing to go.<br>
- Its low risk of screwing up my setup.<br>
- It costs nothing to maintain (unless your alts are on seperate accounts you bought <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
<br>
